mutation

Class MutationManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • mutation.MutationManager

  • public class MutationManager
extends java.lang.Object
    An operator that impose conformational changes (mutations in the GA jargon) on proteins. To this end it uses libraries of predefined, self avoiding local mutations. Each library includes mutations of the same length.

      • addLibraryEntry

        private void addLibraryEntry(Mutation mutation,
                   MutationLibrary library)
        Adds a mutation to a MutationLibrary. Six versions of of each mutation are added to mutationLibrary entry. the method fill's for the given mutation all the possible vector in the given rotations

        0 degrees on axis x

        90 degrees on axis x

        -90 degrees on axis x

        180 degrees on axis x

        90 degrees on axis y

        -90 degrees on axis y

        Parameters:
        mutation - the mutation
        library - the mutationLibrary

      • mutate

        public void mutate(Protein protein,
          Protein out,
          int max_tries)
        Parameters:
        protein - - mutation will be created from this protein
        out - - protein with low fitness. if mutation process is successful out will become the result of of the mutation, else out will be reset.
        max_tries - - max tries for creating a mutation.
